label: Weight
codebookDescription: Weight measured using standardized technique (calibrated scale)

label: Study timepoint
definition: 5 year study with observations at year 1, 3 & 5.

label: Hookworm, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of hookworm infection in a study participant, based on detection of at least one parasite egg in any of the stool samples. Up to three stool samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. Two slides were prepared from each stool sample using the Kato-Katz method and examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.

label: Schistosoma mansoni infection intensity, by microscopy
definition: Schistosoma mansoni infection intensity, in mean eggs per gram (EPG) of feces, from all slides examined for a study participant. Up to three stool samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. Two slides were prepared from each stool sample using the Kato-Katz method and examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.
codebookDescription: Mean Schistosoma mansoni infection intensity (eggs per gram of stool): arithmetic mean of sm1a_epg, sm1b_epg, sm2a_epg, sm2b_epg, sm3a_epg, sm3b_epg
